15/06/2007
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- NATO Secretary-General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer told an informal meeting with NATO defence ministers Thursday (June 14th) that KFOR is ready to respond to any challenge to Kosovo's security. 
De Hoop Scheffer said the Alliance is watching developments closely and remains firm in its support for UN envoy Martti Ahtisaari's proposal. 
(RFE, Balkanweb, RTK, Telegrafi, Kosovalive - 14/06/07)
